summary: is anyone aside from taliesin openly queer in the cast? was just scrolling through ashley's tumblr and she has several posts...
question: is anyone aside from taliesin openly queer in the cast? was just scrolling through ashley's tumblr and she has several posts reblogged (one that I'd say is like almost pinup-esque) of gillian anderson and I don't think straight women do that. being very into gillian or scully is like a wlw staple. I don't want to speculate cos that's rude, just wondering if you knew anything :) thanks for your great posts!
answer:
As far as I know, Taliesin’s the only one who’s openly labelled himself as LGBTQ+. Several other cast members (Liam, Marisha, and maybe Matt) have talked about having same-gender encounters when they were younger, but I don’t know if they’ve put a label on it. I don’t know anything about Ashley. 

And thank you :)

summary: I don't really know how to phrase this, but ever since Caduceus "I am so sure" i keep flashing back to Caleb's "I was so sure...
question: I don't really know how to phrase this, but ever since Caduceus "I am so sure" i keep flashing back to Caleb's "I was so sure (until I wasn't)". Just the first part of this sentence has become so synonymous with his backstory that it has been referenced in countless fanart, and on the one hand I know that sometimes things are just worded the same way but on the other hand it feels so deliberate that it makes me think.
answer:
I don’t think you’re wrong, I think it’s very possible that it’s deliberate! 

I think it’s possible that Taliesin (ooc) was suggesting the danger of Caduceus’s certainty, at least in Caduceus’s own mind, by linking it to the effects of Bren’s absolute trust in the Empire. 

On the other hand, a more optimistic reading of it is that Taliesin (ooc, again), was positioning Caduceus as a foil to Caleb/Bren, to send a (meta) message that not all certainty is wrong, though it can be scary to try to know the difference. Bren’s certainty might have led to wrong choices, but that doesn’t mean that Caduceus’s has to. 

Or it could just be a coincidence! But I still think it’s fun to read into these things :)

summary: “I’ve Got My Head in the Clouds”
title: “I’ve Got My Head in the Clouds”
body:
I had to do it. I had to. @luckthebard‘s critrole Crazy-Ex-Girlfriend au is rapidly turning into one of my favorite things. So, a Jester version of I’ve Got My Head in the Clouds!

Note: the duplicity part with it turning into a duet was something of my own doing

JESTER:

I’ve got my head in the clouds
‘Cause that’s where the Traveler is
No longer stuck in the muck on the ground
I figured out how to live
It’s with my head in the clouds
Got no cares anymore
No obligations are holding me down
That’s what the Traveler is for!

[spoken]
Have you ever heard of the Traveler?
I have now, Cleric Me!

Reality was getting so complicated
All the drama was getting insane
But now I defer to the Traveler
So, I’ve lit my Sacred Flame!
The Traveler is my Guiding Bolt

I’ve got my head in the clouds
Blessed with a permanent smile
I am just a leetle bloo tiefling
Bringing about mischief in style!

The Traveler is the tits!

Life has been a blur
Since I’ve met the Traveler!

TRAVELER, spoken:
Did someone say Traveler?

JESTER, spoken:
Whoa, that’s what you look like?

TRAVELER, spoken:
It’s what YOU think I look like!
Now, let’s dance!

JESTER, spoken:
Yeah!

[instrumental]

TRAVELER, spoken:
Off to lunch with the Wildmother!

JESTER:
My life is uncloaked
Cause now I’ve invoked

[spoken]
DUPLICITY!

BOTH JESTERS:
My life will be splendid
Now that I’ve transcended

JESTER:
When scares are infinity

DUPLICATE:
Then Channel Divinity

JESTER:
I’m a-singing out loud
With my head in the

BOTH JESTERS:
Clouds!

body:
widomauk beauty and beast au but not how you think

caleb is the “beast” and molly “the beauty”

caleb is a prince who lives alone in a castle

molly is an amnesiac who stumbles across the castle and decides to stay

caleb is not amused

caleb uses his magic to animate the furniture etc

he still has frumpkin his only companion

molly tries to find out why caleb is here all alone but can’t get him to open up

his magic went awry and he killed his parents while they slept which is why the east wing is burnt and off limits caleb has spent every moment since trying to discover magic to turn back time

molly and caleb fall in love

mob comes to kill molly for past “crimes” and caleb protects him
